				Actually &quot;massive multiplayer&quot; isn't about grouping as much as it means that multiple amounts of people log onto a site that provides them a setting to play within. As for the 'social' aspects of the game. One can 'socialize' without having to group. Just because you go someplace in RL doesn't necessarily mean you have to group with anyone. You can merely go there and communicate for a while and then be on your merry way. The idea of forced 'grouping' I feel should not be implemented. Not everyone (including myself) enjoys grouping. As I have experienced in the past (unless you group with your RL friends in the game) many of the people I have encountered in groups were either egotistical, immature, or just downright annoying (I didn't say all, just many of the people I have encountered.) Now don't get me wrong, there are quite a few people out there that were a joy to be around with... but I'm sorry to say, those people are few and far between.
