				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   I do not at all see them saying &quot;Soloing will be harder&quot; or &quot;Soloers will get less exp&quot; at all.  They are merely saying, in short, exp gain is probably getting bigger for grouping also killing higher lvl mobs than light blues will get you more exp Grouping OR Solo.  So if you and 4 buddies kill a mob 7 levels higher than your highest level player in the group, you will get, I am guessing, MUCH more exp; or if you solo a mob 3 levels higher than you you will see a gain in exp as well.  Quote:&quot;The intent is to promote grouping, !!not to inflict a harsh nerf on our more casual players who frequently do not have the time to invest in finding and forming a group.!!&quot; = Better bonus for grouping and no loss for soloers.  Another quote:&quot;we do not believe that going solo should be !!the single most optimal way!! to gain experience in EverQuest, which is what it had become prior to these changes.&quot;.  Restates my above point.<BR>
<BR>
   Soloers be calm for I am one as well.  I don't think we will see any exp drop for us, just a gain if we decide to group for a bit, and even better, KILL THOSE REDS for a nice bonus.<BR>
